{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-index-js","path":"/","result":{"data":{"hero":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Hello World! My name is","name":"Chhayansh Purohit","subtitle":"I love exploring new things!","buttonText":"Contact Me"},"html":"<p>I'm an Data Science and Cyber Security Enthusiast with a goal-driven creative mindset and passion for learning and innovating.</p>\n<p>Currently pursuing my MS in Information Technology and Management from <a href=\"https://www.utdallas.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The University of Texas at Dallas.</a>.</p>\n<p>Outside work, I love adventure sports and aim to travel the world.</p>"}}]},"about":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"About Me","avatar":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":0.9831460674157303,"src":"/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/ea4ab/profile.jpg","srcSet":"/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/477ba/profile.jpg 175w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/06776/profile.jpg 350w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/ea4ab/profile.jpg 700w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/3055e/profile.jpg 1050w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/eff08/profile.jpg 1400w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/c122a/profile.jpg 1900w","srcWebp":"/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/89afa/profile.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/9fca7/profile.webp 175w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/37a4e/profile.webp 350w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/89afa/profile.webp 700w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/78e7a/profile.webp 1050w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/03d34/profile.webp 1400w,\n/static/2f77904810dab259a63bfa35895129f4/a4666/profile.webp 1900w","sizes":"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"}}},"skills":["dgd"]},"html":"<p>If you are reading this, believe me, “<strong>Dreaming, after all, is a form of planning and Dreams do come True!!</strong>” And with that note, let me walk you through my career path and how my interest in technology lead me to where I am today :)</p>\n<p>I have a strong passion for using technology to solve the world's biggest problems one byte at a time. As a technologist, I have expertise in Data Science and Analytics, Cyber Security, Software Engineering, finding trends in the data and Program Management.</p>\n<p>All these skills are aquired over the years. Interestingly, I got introduced to programming and data science in my freshman year at <a href=\"https://www.jecjabalpur.ac.in/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Jabalpur Engineering College, Jabalpur</a> where I completed my Bachelors of Technology in Computer Science and Engineering (2017-2021).</p>\n<p>I joined <a href=\"https://www.infosys.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Infosys Ltd</a> as a Data Engineer contracted to <a href=\"https://www.pfizer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Pfizer</a>. Developed  Pfizer Registry Quality Control Management System, a Rules Engine for changed data capture and logic rule check using SQL database and Alteryx workflows.</p>\n<p>Decided to get into Techno-Management and flew to the States (USA) to get my Master's of Science in Information Technology and Management from <a href=\"https://www.utdallas.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The University of Texas at Dallas.</a></p>\n<p>Here is a list of the technologies that I'm familiar with!</p>"}}]},"jobs":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Data Engineer","company":"Infosys","range":"Sept 2021 - June 2022","url":"https://www.infosys.com/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Responsible for code development, UAT support, automation of Bell Canada NM1-RTB customisation project as part of Digital Delivery scrum team. (Oct 2021 - present)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Part of Walk-the-Tech Go team of 10 developers building a microservice in Go language. Tech stack includes Couchbase, Go echo framework, REST APIs implementation, JMeter and Postman for testing purposes.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Selected as one of the 15 Amdocs India Innovation Agents with the least industry experience in years.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Responsible for code development as a developer of Amdocs Technology BSS-B2B Billing &#x26; RTB scrum team. (Nov 2020 - Oct 2021)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Certified in Agile, <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/133QWdIhw9KI0YMKs1SPI_6VQ1ENtMiCe/view?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">DevOps</a>, and MS360 architecture.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Systems Intern","company":"CCL","range":"May - June 2019","url":"http://www.centralcoalfields.in/ind/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Project on developing a fully working dynamic eCommerce website using PHP and MySQL.</li>\n<li>Prepared a complete report about the specifications and working of the software.</li>\n<li>View <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Cn6gxJ1UYpcdz97FivBBp-SsXiVbgg5-/view?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">PROJECT REPORT</a> and <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1R1in-IgfDj9qx9btWEeA_9Ob3db-54_c/view?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CERTIFICATE</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Research Intern","company":"XLRI","range":"May - June 2018","url":"https://www.xlri.ac.in/"},"html":"<ul>\n<li>Meta analysis and a literature review on the topics 'Knowledge Hiding', 'Ethical Leadership', 'Ethical Culture', 'Ethical Climate' and 'Unethical Behaviour'.</li>\n<li>Maintained the data in MS Excel and represented the trend via R programming.</li>\n<li>Work done under Prof. Jatinder Kr. Jha of HR department of XLRI.</li>\n<li>View <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1RlOPvA1EmE24aQMWeSiXbB3N36CUizXA/view?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CERTIFICATE</a></li>\n</ul>"}}]},"featured":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Face Mask Detection","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.1341463414634148,"src":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/fa839/face-mask.png","srcSet":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/847ef/face-mask.png 175w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/91cba/face-mask.png 350w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/fa839/face-mask.png 555w","srcWebp":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/3745e/face-mask.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/9fca7/face-mask.webp 175w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/37a4e/face-mask.webp 350w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/3745e/face-mask.webp 555w","sizes":"(max-width: 555px) 100vw, 555px"}}},"tech":["OpenCV","TensorFlow","Keras","Python"],"github":"https://github.com/chhayanshp11/Face-Mask-Detection","external":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AAkNyZlUae0"},"html":"<p>Face Mask Detection system to detect face masks in static images as well as in real-time video streams. Own custom dataset was built using Bing Search API and Kaggle.</p>\n<p>Inspired by Adrian Rosebrock's <a href=\"https://www.pyimagesearch.com/2020/05/04/covid-19-face-mask-detector-with-opencv-keras-tensorflow-and-deep-learning/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">PyImageSearch Blog</a>.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"GirlScript Twitter Bot","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.1341463414634148,"src":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/fa839/bot.png","srcSet":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/847ef/bot.png 175w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/91cba/bot.png 350w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/fa839/bot.png 555w","srcWebp":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/3745e/bot.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/9fca7/bot.webp 175w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/37a4e/bot.webp 350w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/3745e/bot.webp 555w","sizes":"(max-width: 555px) 100vw, 555px"}}},"tech":["Python","tweepy","Twitter API"],"github":"https://github.com/chhayanshp11/Girlscript-Twitter-Bot","external":"https://twitter.com/girlscript_bot"},"html":"<p>A Twitter Bot for <a href=\"https://www.girlscript.tech/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">GirlScript Foundation</a> that automatically retweets, favourites the tweets and follows the users who tweet with hashtag #girlscript. Checkout my tech blog on how to create it <a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/how-to-make-a-twitter-bot-in-python/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">HERE</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Caim Consulting","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.1341463414634148,"src":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/fa839/demo1.png","srcSet":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/847ef/demo1.png 175w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/91cba/demo1.png 350w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/fa839/demo1.png 555w","srcWebp":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/3745e/demo1.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/9fca7/demo1.webp 175w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/37a4e/demo1.webp 350w,\n/static/2af3495c457929649778989f21440ccb/3745e/demo1.webp 555w","sizes":"(max-width: 555px) 100vw, 555px"}}},"tech":["HTML","CSS","Javascript","Bootstrap"],"github":"https://github.com/caimconsulting/caim-consulting-website","external":"https://caimconsulting.in/"},"html":"<p>Collaborated with the <a href=\"https://caimconsulting.in/developers/?\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Developer Team</a> to develop the front-end and deploy the website on Heroku for a pro-bono legal startup <a href=\"https://caimconsulting.in/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Caim Consulting</a>.</p>"}}]},"projects":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Learn Beginner Golang","tech":["Go","Rest API"],"github":"https://github.com/chhayanshp11/learning-easy-golang","external":""},"html":"<p>Collection of small code gists along my Golang learning journey</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Kubernetes Handbook","tech":["Kubernetes"],"github":"https://github.com/chhayanshp11/kubernetes-handbook","external":"https://amdocs-1.gitbook.io/kubernetes-handbook/"},"html":"<p>This handbook covers a beginner-friendly detailed understanding of Kubernetes core concepts.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"IntelliJ Idea Tips & Tricks","tech":["IntelliJ Idea"],"github":"https://github.com/chhayanshp11/IntelliJ-Idea-Tips-n-Tricks","external":"https://chhayanshp11.github.io/IntelliJ-Idea-Tips-n-Tricks/"},"html":"<p>IntelliJ Idea Tips and Tricks for Java/Spring Microservices Handling</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"100DaysOfCode","tech":["Kotlin/Java","Spring Microservices","Javascript","CSS","Python"],"github":"https://github.com/chhayanshp11/100DaysOfCode","external":""},"html":"<p>Repository dedicated to my #100DaysOfCode journey</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Portfolio Website v1","tech":["HTML","CSS","Javascript","Bootstrap"],"github":"https://github.com/chhayanshp11/chhayanshp11.github.io-v1","external":"https://chhayanshp11.github.io/chhayanshp11.github.io-v1/"},"html":"<p>Portfolio Website Version 1 hosted using GitHub Pages. Updates coming soon!</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Face Recognition in Python","tech":["Python","OpenCV","Pillow","NumPy"],"github":"https://github.com/chhayanshp11/Face-Recognition-in-Python","external":""},"html":"<p>A real time face recognition system developed in Python using Pillow, OpenCV and NumPy libraries</p>"}}]},"contact":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Get In Touch","buttonText":"Mail Me"},"html":"<p>As a result of continuous improvement, I believe in learning.\nAnd to learn together, let’s get connected!</p>\n<p>My inbox is always open. Whether you have a question or just want to say hello, I'll try my best to get back to you! Feel free to mail me about any relevant job updates.</p>"}}]}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["3115057458"]}